<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-83-1100 </DOCNO><TEXT>Tests connected with the preparation and use of coal-water mixtures (CWM)in asphalt mixing plants were carried out within the scope of the ROeG/DEUTAG/TEERBAUworking association. CWM burners and feed systems were developed in cooperationwith two burner manufacturers to permit CWM to be used in this field,as a substitute for conventional sources of energy, such as oil, gasor pulverized brown coal. An average specific energy input was attainedof brown coal. An average specific energy input was attained of 100 kWh/tdried and heated mineral matter by modifying the drying drums and optimizingthe auxiliary fuel portion. 4 figs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>